Despite the best of intensions, errors happen. I am keeping this list up-to-date in case errors can be fixed with reprints and new editions. If you see errors, I would be grateful if you could email me to let me know.

1. Seema Sheth: The red flower in Fig 8.7 is Erythranthe verbenacea, which grows in Arizona. This is not a photo of Mimulus cardinalis. 
The pink flower is Erythranthe lewisii (from the Rockies/PNW), and Erythranthe erubescens is the current name of Mimulus lewisii which was part of Angert's work.

